-- Baotou Steel Union Says Board of Directors Accepts Chairman's Resignation
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-13T23:55:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/baotou-steel-union-says-board-of-directors-accepts-chairman-s-resignation.html

          
          
             Inner Mongolian Baotou Steel Union
Co.’s board of directors accepted the resignation of Chairman
Cui Chen, the company said in a statement to Shanghai’s stock
exchange without giving a reason for the resignation.  
 The company has appointed Zhou Bingli as its new chairman,
according to the statement. Baotou Steel Union also appointed
Meng Zhiquan as president, according to the statement, which
didn’t say if Meng was replacing an executive.  
